name: Alioramus

name: Allosaurus

name: Alphadon

name: Apatosaurus
description: the Dinosaur with a Secret Identity! Say hello to one of the biggest animals to ever walk the Earth! The plant-eating Apatosaurus was a truly massive dinosaur. Its name, which means Deceptive Lizard, is one of the coolest in science because it tells an amazing story. Over a century ago, during the famous Bone Wars of the late 1800s, two famous fossil hunters thought they had discovered two different dinosaurs: Apatosaurus and Brontosaurus. They were both huge, long-necked beasts! Soon, scientists decided these two names belonged to just one dino. Apatosaurus was the official winner, and Brontosaurus vanished! But hold on—the mystery isn't over! In a thrilling modern twist, new research has convinced many paleontologists that Brontosaurus was a real, unique dinosaur all along! It’s a scientific comeback story! This long-running debate is proof that even in science, there are still exciting legends waiting to be revived

naming.etymology: (Greek: apatos 'deceptive', due to a misplaced vertebra)

name: Araeoscelis

description: a small marine snake. It was one of the earliest known snakes to live in the ocean

name: Pachyrhinosaurus
description: a large horned dinosaur that had a thick, bumpy boss instead of a horn on its nose

name: Palaelodus
description: a flamingo-like bird. It had a short, slender neck and long legs for wading

name: Palaeobatrachus
description: an ancient frog, an early relative of modern frogs

name: Palaeoniscum
description: a small fish with a long, slender body

name: Palaeospondylus
description: a small, eel-like fish. It's a mystery to scientists because it had a long, slender body but no jaws or fins

name: Palaeotrionyx
description: a small turtle with a broad shell and a long tail

name: Panoplosaurus
description: an armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Pantylus
description: a small amphibian with a short tail and short legs

name: Paracyclotosaurus
description: a large amphibian with a very broad, flat head

name: Parasaurolophus
description: a duck-billed dinosaur with a huge, backward-pointing tube on its head, which may have been used for making loud calls

name: Pareiasaurus
description: a large, robust reptile that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Peloneustes
description: a pliosaur, a short-necked marine reptile with a large head and powerful jaws

name: Peltobatrachus
description: a small, armored amphibian with bony plates on its back

name: Perleidus
description: a small fish with a long, slender body

name: Petrolacosaurus
description: one of the earliest known diapsids. It was a small, lizard-like reptile with a long tail and slender legs

name: Pharyngolepis
description: a small, jawless fish with a well-developed dorsal fin

name: Phorusrhacus
description: the "terror bird". It was a giant predator, with a massive beak and strong legs for running

name: Phthinosuchus
description: a small meat-eater

name: Pisanosaurus
description: small, and is thought to be one of the most primitive members of the group of plant-eating dinosaurs

name: Pistosaurus
description: a small, lizard-like reptile that was a close relative of the nothosaurs

name: Placochelys
description: a small, turtle-like reptile with a broad, flat shell that looked like a turtle's

name: Placodus
description: one of the first placodonts, with strong, flat teeth for crushing shells

name: Planocephalosaurus
description: a small, lizard-like reptile. It was an early relative of the modern Tuatara and likely hunted insects

name: Platecarpus
description: a large marine lizard and powerful swimmer, a type of mosasaur

name: Plateosaurus
description: one of the first really big plant-eaters. It had a long neck and tail and strong back legs

name: Platyhystrix
description: an ancient, stocky amphibian (like a large salamander) that had a tall, flat, bony sail on its back, possibly to help it warm up or cool down

name: Platysomus
description: a small fish with a deep, flat body

name: Plesiosaurus
description: the first plesiosaur ever found! Its most distict features were its long neck, small head, and big flippers!

naming.etymology: (Greek: plesios 'near', thought to be closer to crocodiles than ichthyosaurs)

name: Pleurosaurus
description: a small, lizard-like marine reptile with a long body and slender limbs

name: Pliosaurus
description: a large, short-necked plesiosaur with a massive head and powerful jaws

naming.etymology: (Greek: pleiōn 'more', implying it was more evolved than Plesiosaurus)

name: Plotosaurus
description: another large mosasaur with a long body and tail, and was a fast swimmer

name: Polacanthus
description: an armored dinosaur with a large shield over its hips

name: Postosuchus
description: a large, heavily built predator that could walk on two legs

name: Prenocephale
description: a pachycephalosaur with a high, domed head, smaller than its famous relative

name: Presbyornis
description: a duck-like bird

name: Pristichampsus
description: a large, robust crocodile that lived on land and had powerful jaws and hoof-like claws, suggesting it was a fast runner

name: Procompsognathus
description: a small, bipedal carnivorous theropod from the late Triassic period

name: Procynosuchus
description: a small, semi-aquatic reptile

name: Proganochelys
description: one of the earliest turtles, with a heavily armored shell

name: Prosaurolophus
description: a duck-billed dinosaur with a small, solid crest on its head

name: Proterosuchus
description: an early reptile, an ancestor to crocodiles and dinosaurs, that looked like a large lizard with a distinctive, strong, hooked snout for catching prey

name: Protorosaurus
description: a medium-sized reptile with a long, slender body and a long tail

name: Protostega
description: a giant sea turtle! One of the largest turtles ever

name: Protosuchus
description: a small, robust crocodile. It looked like a mix between a modern crocodile and a lizard

name: Pteranodon
description: a very large pterosaur with a wingspan of up to 24 feet. It had a long, bony crest on its head and a toothless beak, and it was a big fish-eater

name: Pteraspis
description: a typical pteraspids with a head shield covered in small bony plates

name: Pterodactylus
description: a small pterosaur with a wingspan of about 2.5 feet. It had a short tail and was one of the first pterosaurs ever discovered

name: Pterodaustro
description: a medium-sized pterosaur with a wingspan of over 7 feet. It had a beak filled with tons of bristle-like teeth, which it used to filter tiny creatures from the water, just like a flamingo!

name: Pteronisculus
description: a small fish with a long, slender body

name: Ptilodus
description: a small, squirrel-like mammal. It had a long tail and sharp teeth

name: Purgatorius
description: a small, shrew-like mammal. It is considered an early ancestor of primates

name: Pycnodus
description: a small fish with a deep, flat body and crushing teeth for eating hard-shelled prey

name: Quetzalcoatlus
description: a gigantic pterosaur with a wingspan of up to 39 feet. It was one of the largest flying animals ever to exist!

naming.etymology: (Named after the Aztec feathered serpent god Quetzalcoatl)

name: Rhamphorhynchus
description: a medium-sized pterosaur with a wingspan of 3 feet. Its long tail had a special diamond-shaped fin on the end. It also ate fish

name: Riojasaurus
description: a large dino. It had a heavy body and strong legs, which means it likely walked on all fours most of the time

name: Robertia
description: a small plant-eater, one of the earliest dicynodonts

name: Rutiodon
description: a large, crocodile-like reptile. It was a fish-eater with a long, slender snout

name: Saichania
description: an armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Saltasaurus
description: a medium-sized sauropod. It's one of the most interesting sauropods because it was covered in bony plates, like a dinosaur with armor!

name: Saltopus
description: a very small, agile dinosaur

name: Sarcosuchus
description: a gigantic crocodile, one of the largest crocodiles ever to live

name: Saurichthys
description: a fish with a long, thin body and a long, pointed snout

name: Saurolophus
description: a duck-billed dinosaur with a solid, backward-pointing spike on its head

name: Sauropelta
description: an armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Saurornithoides
description: a medium-sized, intelligent hunter, with a large brain and eyes

name: Saurornitholestes
description: a small, bird-like hunter

name: Scapanorhynchus
description: a shark with a long, pointed snout like a goblin shark today

name: Scaphognathus
description: a small pterosaur with a wingspan of about 3 feet. It had a deep head and a short snout

name: Scutellosaurus
description: a tiny, 4-foot-long dino. It had a surprise—bony plates on its back, making it an early armored dinosaur

name: Scutosaurus
description: a large, robust reptile with a short tail and stout legs

name: Seymouria
description: so similar to reptiles that scientists once thought it was one!

name: Shantungosaurus
description: the largest duck-billed dinosaur ever found

name: Shonisaurus
description: a giant ichthyosaur. It had a long, slender body and a long tail

naming.etymology: (Named for the Shoshone Mountains in Nevada)

name: Silvisaurus
description: an armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Sordes
description: a tiny pterosaur with a wingspan of only 1.5 feet. Fossils show it had a fuzzy covering, which might mean it was warm-blooded!

name: Spathobatis
description: a ray with a broad, flat body with a long tail and large fins

name: Sphenacodon
description: a meat-eating reptile with a deep, narrow skull and sharp teeth

name: Spinosaurus
description: an enormous hunter. It was possibly the largest carnivorous dinosaur ever and is famous for its massive sail

naming.etymology: (Latin: spina 'spine' + Greek: sauros 'lizard', referring to its neural spines)

name: Stagonolepis
description: heavily armored and had a pig-like snout

name: Stegoceras
description: a small pachycephalosaur. It had a cool, dome-shaped skull

name: Stegosaurus
description: a large plant-eater famous for its huge plates and spiked tail

naming.etymology: (Greek: stegē 'roof/plate' + sauros 'lizard', referring to its back plates)

name: Stenonychosaurus
description: a medium-sized hunter. It had the largest brain for its body size of any dinosaur

name: Stenopterygius
description: a common ichthyosaur, with a dolphin-like body shape

name: Stethacanthus
description: famous for a weird, flat, anvil-shaped fin on its back

name: Strunius
description: was a tiny, stubby-bodied fish that swam during the late Devonian period. Despite its small size, it was a ferocious predator whose super-strong, hinged skull helped it bite and crush the armor of other small fish

name: Struthiosaurus
description: a small armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

name: Stupendemys
description: a stupendously large turtle, about the size of a car!

name: Styracosaurus
description: a large horned dinosaur with a huge nose horn and a frill with long spikes around the edge

name: Supersaurus
description: a gigantic sauropod. It was one of the longest dinosaurs ever found

name: Talarurus
description: an armored dinosaur that was heavily built with a short tail and stout legs

naming.etymology: (Greek: talaron 'wicker basket', referring to its tail club)

name: Tanystropheus
description: a medium-sized reptile with a short body but an extremely long neck

name: Tarbosaurus
description: a very large tyrannosaur, very similar to T. rex

name: Teleosaurus
description: a large, marine crocodile with a long snout, perfect for snatching up fish

name: Temnodontosaurus
description: a medium-sized ichthyosaur. It had a long, slender body and a long tail

name: Tenontosaurus
description: a large, plant-eating dinosaur known for its very long tail

naming.etymology: (Greek: tenōn 'sinew', referring to its ossified tendons)

name: Teratosaurus
description: a very large, meat-eating reptile, but not a dinosaur! It belonged to a group called Rauisuchians and was one of the top predators of the Late Triassic period

name: Terrestrisuchus
description: a small, slender crocodile. It had long legs and a long tail for a life on the ground

name: Testudo
description: similar to modern tortoises. It had a broad shell and a short tail

name: Thadeosaurus
description: a small, lizard-like marine reptile also built for a life in the water

name: Thecodontosaurus
description: a tiny European dinosaur. It was one of the first dinosaurs ever discovered!

name: Thelodus
description: a small fish covered in tiny bony scales

name: Thescelosaurus
description: a small, plant-eating dinosaur with a long tail and short legs

name: Thrinaxodon
description: a small, carnivorous cynodont, an important transitional fossil showing mammal-like traits

name: Ticinosuchus
description: a large, quadrupedal archosaur, a crocodile-line predator

naming.etymology: (Named for the Ticino River in Switzerland)

name: Titanosuchus
description: a large, carnivorous dinocephalian, a 'terrible crocodile

name: Torosaurus
description: a large horned dinosaur with the largest frill of any known land animal

naming.etymology: (Greek: toros 'perforated/pierced' + sauros 'lizard', referring to holes in its frill)

name: Tremataspis
description: a small fish with a huge, flat, shovel-shaped head shield that covered most of its body

name: Triadobatrachus
description: considered the oldest and most primitive relative of modern frogs. It was small, had a frog-like head, long hind legs, but still had a short tail!

naming.etymology: (Named for the Triassic period + Greek: batrachos 'frog')

name: Triceratops
description: a large horned dinosaur with three horns on its face and a massive frill

name: Tristychius
description: a small, slender shark with a long tail and two dorsal fins

name: Tsintaosaurus
description: a duck-billed dinosaur with a long, rod-like crest that stuck straight up from its head

name: Tuojiangosaurus
description: a large plant-eater famous for its huge plates and spiked tail

naming.etymology: (Named for the Tuo River in China)

name: Tyrannosaurus
description: the most famous giant! With a huge head, powerful jaws, and tiny two-fingered arms

name: Varanosaurus
description: an early pelycosaur, a synapsid with a long snout resembling a monitor lizard

naming.etymology: (Named for its resemblance to modern monitor lizards, *Varanus*)

name: Velociraptor
description: a small but fierce hunter, also with a large sickle claw

name: Vieraella
description: one of the earliest known frogs

name: Wuerhosaurus
description: a large plant-eater famous for its huge plates and spiked tail

naming.etymology: (Named for the Wuerho area in China)

name: Xenacanthus
description: an eel-like shark with a long dorsal fin and a spine on its head

name: Yinlong Downsi
description: a small, early horned dinosaur

name: Zalambdalestes
description: a small, shrew-like mammal. It had a long snout and sharp teeth

naming.etymology: (Referring to the shape of one of its teeth)
